Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present 1, 1A & 1B Spruson Street, Neutral Bay. 1, 1A & 1B Spruson Street is a premium elevated development site positioned in one of Neutral Bay's most desirable locations, with water views of Neutral Bay through to the Sydney Harbour Bridge and CBD. The property boasts a total land holding of 992sqm*. The property’s R4 High Density Residential zoning and 12m Height Limit, creates a sought-after opportunity for a high-end residential development (STCA). This is reassured by the strong demand for luxury apartments from local affluent downsizers. Additional access to the property is available via Boyd Lane, allowing for more flexible design options and a more seamless construction process. 

Lifestyle location with Spruson Street Road Reserve situated on its doorstep, sitting above a set of stairs that run down to Anderson Park and the sparkling water of Neutral Bay. The pristine white sands of Hayes Street Beach are just a short stroll away, as well as harbour foreshore walks from Kurraba Point to Shell Cove and the MacCallum Seawater Pool. The popular restaurants and cafes of Kirribilli are also within close proximity. Metres to bus services and Neutral Bay Wharf with ferry services to North Sydney and Circular Quay. Milsons Point train station is just a 20 minute* stroll, providing transport to Sydney CBD and greater North Shore.


1, 1A & 1B Spruson Street, Neutral Bay benefits from the following key attributes:

- Substantial 992sqm* land offering
- Elevated position with views of Neutral Bay, Sydney Harbour Bridge and Sydney CBD
- R4 High Density Residential zoning and 12m Height Limit permitting with consent a high-end luxury apartment block development (STCA)
- 25m* frontage to Spruson Street and 14m* frontage to Boyd Lane
- Strong demand for luxury apartments from local affluent downsizers
- Lifestyle location with Spruson Street Road Reserve on its doorstep, sitting above a set of stairs that run down to Anderson Park and the sparkling waters of Neutral Bay. The pristine white sands of Hayes Street Beach are just a short
stroll away, as well as harbour foreshore walks
- Close to popular restaurants and cafes of Kirribilli
- Located less than 1km* from North Sydney CBD and 3.8km* to Sydney CBD
- Great accessibility, moments to bus, ferry and train services to North Sydney and Sydney CBD


1, 1A & 1B Spruson Street, Neutral Bay will be made available for sale by way of Expressions of Interest closing Wednesday, 15 September 2021 at 4pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

CBRE, as the exclusive listing agent is pleased to present 6 Thrupp Street, Neutral Bay. Designed by renowned architecture firm, Cracknell & Lonergan Architects, 6 Thrupp Street, Neutral Bay is a DA approved luxury development site for 4 x 3 bedroom apartments. The development consists of oversized apartments with modern finishes, sitting on a generous 669sqm* parcel of land. Designed to seek the highest and best use of the site using high quality, modern architecture whilst focusing on amenity and offering exposure to natural light. The approved apartments, 2 on each floor, comprising 3 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms, will have only one common wall and enjoy three sides of natural light. The apartments on level one benefit from 2 large balconies, whilst the ground floor apartments include 2 patio areas and a large private lawn. Lifestyle location close to eateries, Hayes Street Beach, Neutral Bay Wharf, Anderson Park, Harriette Street Road Reserve, Mosman Bay and bus services to Cremorne and Neutral Bay Junction.

6 Thrupp Street, Neutral Bay benefits from the following key attributes:

•DA Approval for 4 luxury 3 bedroom apartments
•Approved GFA of 413.08sqm*
•Generous 669sqm* land offering
•Designed by designed by Cracknell & Lonergan Architects to seek the highest and best use of the site
•Lifestyle location close to eateries, Hayes Street Beach, Neutral Bay Wharf, and bus services

Residing in a quiet leafy street, the property presents the opportunity to strata title and sell down or develop into a luxury apartment block under existing use rights (STCA). Standing on a generous 657sqm* landholding, the charming property is comprised of six-two-bedroom half floor apartments with six onsite parking spaces. The apartments being half floors, enjoy only one common wall and great natural light from windows across three sides. Situated in an extremely convenient and desirable location just moments from the bustling North Sydney CBD and Sydney CBD in addition to major services and amenities including shops, public transport, prestigious schools, and lavish parks.

Key features of the property include:

•Six spacious half floor two-bedroom apartments recently renovated.
•Each apartment has its own car space with onsite parking for six cars
•Opportunity to strata title and sell down or develop under existing use rights (STCA)
•Sensational investment opportunity in a highly tenanted area, underwriting the area’s strong rental demand
•Highly desirable and popular location attracting white collar tenants and young families
•Conveniently situated in Sydney’s exclusive Lower North Shore in great proximity to shops, prestigious schools, public transport, parks, and Sydney CBD

•Generous 657sqm* landholding in a quiet street
